# Repo-wide default: store LF, check out LF on every platform. Editors that
# save CRLF get normalized at checkin, and working copies stay byte-identical
# to the repo — eliminating autocrlf warnings, phantom diffs after eol-config
# changes, and platform-dependent checkouts. Auto-detection leaves binaries
# untouched. The specific pins below predate this rule and stay because each
# documents a byte-exactness contract that must survive even if the umbrella
# is ever loosened.
* text=auto eol=lf

# CI 在 Linux 上以 bash 执行 .sh,CRLF 会破坏解释器行为——钉死 LF。
*.sh text eol=lf
# D5 firewall ownership evidence pins the byte-exact SHA256 of this tracked
# source; an autocrlf checkout (e.g. Windows CI) must not rewrite its bytes.
scripts/d5-windows-network-packages.json text eol=lf
# Golden vectors are byte-compared against LF regenerations (core/share and
# relay/protocol -update suites); an autocrlf checkout must not rewrite them.
testvectors/*.json text eol=lf
# make recipes run under msys sh; CRLF would leak \r into continuation lines.
Makefile text eol=lf
